This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image restoration and face recognition. The use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of perceptual and adversarial losses, which are commonly used in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper could also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it deals with image processing and restoration.
